[[File:Slipstek-4.jpg|thumb]]
The overhand knot with draw-loop similar to the [[Knots/Stopper knots/Overhand knot|overhand knot]]. It releases with a tug on the free end, which allows it to be untied easily. To tie it, form a loop, then make a bight out of the working end and put it through, tightening by pulling on the standing end.

