{{navigate|Prev=Kingdoms|Next=Kingdoms/Bacteria|NextText=Bacteria}}
==Archea==
[[Image:Colourful_Thermophilic_Archaebacteria_Stain_in_Midway_Geyser_Basin.jpg|thumb|400px|Colorful archea]]
Archea are creatures made up of single cells. They have been on Earth for a long, long time. Their name means old.

Archea have no nucleus in their single cell. They were once called bacteria, but they were taken out of the [[{{ROOTBOOKNAME}}/Kingdoms/Bacteria|kingdom bacteria]] because they are so different.


{{BookCat}}

{{navigate|Prev=Kingdoms/Archaea|PrevText=Archaea|NextText=Protists|Next=Kingdoms/Protists}}
==Bacteria==

'''Bacteria''' are single celled creatures with no nucleus. They are very, very small. They grow all over the Earth, in the ground, in the water, and even in our bodies.

Some bacteria can cause diseases, but most do good things like break down waste and make ''oxygen''.

[[ Image:Bacteriarazorback.jpg]]

{{BookCat}}

{{navigate|Prev=Organs|Next=Systems/Circulatory System|NextText=Circulatory System}}
==Organ systems== [[Image:Scheme_female_reproductive_system-en.svg|thumb|250px|right|Reproductive system in women]] Two or more organs that work together make an '''organ system'''.
Organ systems are found in all different kinds of living things.
Some of the organ systems found in humans include:
*[[{{ROOTBOOKNAME}}/Systems/Circulatory System|Circulatory System]] *[[{{ROOTBOOKNAME}}/Systems/Respiratory System|Respiratory System]] *[[{{ROOTBOOKNAME}}/Systems/Digestive System|Digestive System]] *[[{{ROOTBOOKNAME}}/Systems/Endocrine System|Endocrine System]] *[[{{ROOTBOOKNAME}}/Systems/Reproductive System|Reproductive System]] *[[{{ROOTBOOKNAME}}/Systems/Urinary System|Urinary System]] *[[{{ROOTBOOKNAME}}/Systems/Immune System|Immune System]] *[[{{ROOTBOOKNAME}}/Systems/Muscular System|Muscular System]] *[[{{ROOTBOOKNAME}}/Systems/Skeletal System|Skeletal System]] *[[{{ROOTBOOKNAME}}/Systems/Integumentary System|Integumentary System]] *[[{{ROOTBOOKNAME}}/Systems/Nervous System|Nervous System]]
{{BookCat}}

{{navigate|PrevText=Systems|Prev=Systems|Next=Systems/Respiratory System|NextText=Respiratory System}}
[[Image:Grafik_blutkreislauf.jpg|thumb|right|200px|The Circulatory System]]

==The Circulatory System==

The '''Circulatory System''' moves blood around your body. This blood carries food and ''oxygen'' around to all of the cells of the body. It also carries signals called '''hormones''' that help the body work together.

The major organ of the circulatory system is the '''heart''', which pumps the blood.  Blood goes away from the heart in tubes called '''arteries''' and comes back to the heart in tubes called '''veins'''.  The smallest tubes are called '''capillaries'''.

{{BookCat}}

{{navigate|PrevText=Muscular System|Prev=Systems/Muscular System|Next=Systems/Integumentary System|NextText=Integumentary System}}
==The Skeletal System==
[[Image:Human_skeleton_front_en.svg|thumb|The human skeleton.]]
The '''Skeletal System''' is made of all of the bones in the body.  It protects the [[../Reproductive System|reproductive organs]] and is a place for [[../Muscular System|muscles]] to attach.  Bones are a very important part of the human body.  Without them, we would simply collapse, and be very unstable.  They support all of our tissue and muscles, and they are very difficult to break.

The inside of the bones is called the ''bone marrow''.  This is where most [[../Circulatory System|blood cells]] are made.

{{BookCat}}

{{navigate|PrevText=Reproductive System|Prev=Systems/Reproductive System|Next=Systems/Immune System|NextText=Immune System}}
[[Image:Adrenal_gland_%28PSF%29.jpg|thumb|right|280px|Urinary System]]
==The Urinary System==

The '''Urinary system''' takes bad things out of the blood and washes it out of the body.  This liquid waste is called '''urine'''.  Without the urinary system, poisons would fill up the blood and kill a person.  The '''kidneys''' are [[Wikijunior:Biology/Organs|organs]] that filter the blood and remove poison.  Urine is stored in a bag called the '''bladder''' and it leaves the body through a tube called the '''urethra'''.

{{BookCat}}

{{navigate|Prev=Kingdoms/Animals|PrevText=Animals|Next=Conclusion}}
==Viruses==
[[File:Rotavirus Reconstruction.jpg|thumb|right|A virus called a rotavirus, which can cause diarrhoea.]]
Viruses are much smaller than other living things like [[{{ROOTBOOKNAME}}/Kingdoms/Bacteria|bacteria]], so small that it would take around one hundred viruses laid end to end just to make the length of a bacterium! Viruses are not really alive.  They do not do all of the [[{{ROOTBOOKNAME}}/Introduction#What is life?|things that living things do]].  They can only make more copies of themselves when they are inside living cells.

Viruses often kill [[{{ROOTBOOKNAME}}/Cells|cells]], and also make you ill. Lots of diseases are caused by viruses, the most famous ones being the flu and many colds.

{{BookCat}}

