This text is intended to provide a primer on the skills and techniques that can be used in Criminal trial advocacy. Coverage of the law and rules of courtroom conduct and evidential rules are covered elsewhere in the companion texts.
==Contents==
* [[Canadian Criminal Trial Advocacy/Beginning the Case|Beginning the Case]] * [[Canadian Criminal Trial Advocacy/Collecting the Evidence|Collecting the Evidence]] * [[Canadian Criminal Trial Advocacy/Developing a Theory of the Case|Developing a Theory of the Case]] * [[Canadian Criminal Trial Advocacy/Preparing for Trial|Preparing for Trial]] * [[Canadian Criminal Trial Advocacy/Opening Statements|Opening Statements]] * [[Canadian Criminal Trial Advocacy/Direct Examination|Direct Examination]] * [[Canadian Criminal Trial Advocacy/Exhibits|Exhibits]] * [[Canadian Criminal Trial Advocacy/Cross Examination|Cross Examination]] * [[Canadian Criminal Trial Advocacy/Closing Arguments|Closing Arguments]] * [[Canadian Criminal Trial Advocacy/Appendix|Appendix]]
{{Book Search|prefix=Canadian Criminal Trial Advocacy}}
{{Subjects|Criminal law}} {{alphabetical|C}} {{status|25%}}

==Introduction== The police powers of detention and arrest are some of the most important powers available to a peace officer in their investigation of criminal activity. It is also some of the most invasive powers upon a person's liberty. This is a classic issue of procedural law that circumscribes the peace officers authority in these matters.
These chapters cover not only the powers of police to detain or arrest, but also the right a person has when the police engage in such conduct and remedies for breaches of those rights.
==Topics== * [[Canadian Criminal Procedure and Practice/Arrest and Detention/Investigative Detention|Investigative Detention]] * [[Canadian Criminal Procedure and Practice/Arrest and Detention/Warrant Arrests|Warrant Arrests]] * [[Canadian Criminal Procedure and Practice/Arrest and Detention/Warrantless Arrests|Warrantless Arrests]] * [[Canadian Criminal Procedure and Practice/Arrest and Detention/Arrest Procedure|Arrest Procedure]] ** [[Canadian Criminal Procedure and Practice/Arrest and Detention/Right to Counsel|Right to Counsel]] * [[Canadian Criminal Procedure and Practice/Exclusion of Evidence|Exclusion of Evidence]] * [[Canadian Criminal Procedure and Practice/Waiver of Charter Rights|Waiver of Charter Rights]]
