{{EM software tool |name=IPLT |website=http://www.iplt.org |long description=The Image Processing Library & Toolbox is an open-source project primarily aimed the electron microscopy community, with particular emphasis on 2D electron crystallography. It consists of several modular class libraries written in C++, each exposing a majority of their interface to Python, upon which the processing logic is build. Easy extendability has been a prime focus for the framework design, and we welcome any contribution from the community. |version= |contact=andreas underscore schenk at hms dot harvard dot edu |os support=Linux, Mac OS X, Windows (experimental) |image support=MRC, CCP4, TIFF, JPK, NANOSCOPE, SITUS, PNG, DM3, SPIDER |cost=Free/Open Source |license=[[w:GNU General Public License|GPL]] |program language=[[w:C++|C++]]/[[w:Python_(programming_language)|Python]] |ref1={{cite journal |author=Philippsen A, Schenk AD, Signorell GA, Mariani V, Berneche S, Engel A |title=Collaborative EM image processing with the IPLT image processing library and toolbox |journal=J. Struct. Biol. |volume=157 |issue=1 |pages=28–37 |year=2007 |month=January |pmid=16919967 |doi=10.1016/j.jsb.2006.06.009 |url=}} |ref2={{cite journal |author=Philippsen A, Schenk AD, Stahlberg H, Engel A |title=Iplt--image processing library and toolkit for the electron microscopy community |journal=J. Struct. Biol. |volume=144 |issue=1-2 |pages=4–12 |year=2003 |pmid=14643205 |doi=10.1016/j.jsb.2003.09.032 |url=}} }}
