{{EM software tool |name=Situs |website=http://situs.biomachina.org/ |long description=Situs is a modular software package for the integration of biophysical data across the spatial resolution scales. It has been developed over the last decade with a focus on bridging the resolution gap between atomic structures, coarse-grained models, and volumetric data from low-resolution biophysical origins, such as electron microscopy, tomography, or small-angle scattering. Structural models can be created and refined with various flexible and rigid body docking strategies. The software consists of multiple, stand-alone programs for the format conversion, analysis, visualization, manipulation, and assembly of 3D data sets. |version=2.7 |contact=situs@biomachina.org |os support=Windows, Macintosh, Linux |image support=MRC, CCP4, SITUS, SPIDER, XPLOR, ASCII |cost=Free/Open Source |license=[[w:GNU General Public License|GPL]] |program language=C/C++ |ref1={{Cite journal |first1=W. |last1=Wriggers |coauthors= |year=2010 |title=Using Situs for the Integration of Multi-Resolution Structures |journal=Biophysical Reviews |volume=2 |issue= |pages=21-27 |pmid=20174447 |doi=10.1007/s12551-009-0026-3 |pmcid=PMC2821521 }} |ref2={{cite journal |author=Wriggers W, Chacón P |title=Modeling tricks and fitting techniques for multiresolution structures |journal=Structure |volume=9 |issue=9 |pages=779–88 |year=2001 |month=September |pmid=11566128 |doi= |url=}} |ref3={{cite journal |author=Chacón P, Wriggers W |title=Multi-resolution contour-based fitting of macromolecular structures |journal=J. Mol. Biol. |volume=317 |issue=3 |pages=375–84 |year=2002 |month=March |pmid=11922671 |doi=10.1006/jmbi.2002.5438 |url=}} |ref4={{cite journal |author=Rusu M, Birmanns S, Wriggers W |title=Biomolecular pleiomorphism probed by spatial interpolation of coarse models |journal=Bioinformatics |volume=24 |issue=21 |pages=2460–6 |year=2008 |month=November |pmid=18757874 |pmc=2732278 |doi=10.1093/bioinformatics/btn461 |url=}} }}
{{EM software tool |name=UROX |website=http://sites.google.com/site/xsiebert/urox |long description=An interactive tool for fitting atomic models into electron microscopy reconstructions (or into envelopes derived from small-angle X-ray or neutron scattering). The correlation between the electron density of the atomic models and the map is calculated and updated as a model is moved on the graphical display with the help of the mouse. Calculations are performed in reciprocal-space and the symmetry of the reconstruction is taken into account. The computations are fast and an entire EM reconstruction can be used. Versions above 2.0 include Normal-Modes flexible fitting and "map on map" fitting (in addition to "model in map" fitting). |version=2.0.2 |contact=xsiebert@gmail.com |os support=Linux |image support=EZD, CCP4, MRC, PIF |cost=Free |license= |program language= |ref1={{cite journal |author=Siebert X, Navaza J |title=UROX 2.0: an interactive tool for fitting atomic models into electron-microscopy reconstructions |journal=Acta Crystallogr. D Biol. Crystallogr. |volume=65 |issue=Pt 7 |pages=651–8 |year=2009 |month=July |pmid=19564685 |pmc=2703571 |doi=10.1107/S0907444909008671 |url=}} |ref2={{cite journal |author=Navaza J, Lepault J, Rey FA, Alvarez-Rúa C, Borge J |title=On the fitting of model electron densities into EM reconstructions: a reciprocal-space formulation |journal=Acta Crystallogr. D Biol. Crystallogr. |volume=58 |issue=Pt 10 Pt 2 |pages=1820–5 |year=2002 |month=October |pmid=12351826 |doi= |url=}} }}
